text: Bojan Banjac (Serbian Cyrillic: Бојан Бaњaц, born 24 October 1971 in Inđija) is a former Serbian association footballer. After playing with FK Zemun in the First League of FR Yugoslavia, Banjac moved to France in 1996 where he played 23 Ligue 1 games for Lille OSC in 1996-97 season. ==External links== * * Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:People from Inđija Category:Serbian footballers Category:Serbian expatriate footballers Category:Expatriate footballers in France Category:FK Zemun players Category:Lille OSC players Category:Ligue 1 players Category:Ligue 2 players Category:Association football midfielders
